benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId} - Transfer a bundle to another account

covered: POST: Valid Payload scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC26) demonstrate successful transfers with required and optional fields.

POST: Invalid Payload scenarios (TC08, TC09, TC10, TC11, TC12, TC15, TC16, TC21, TC18, TC19) validate input validation and error handling for bundleId, dates, policies, headers, body presence, and security inputs.
POST: Authorization handling (TC13 and TC11) covers missing/invalid authentication header and unauthorized access.
POST: Server/Dependency error handling (TC14 for 503, TC24 for 500, TC06/TC07 for not found) covers error responses under failure or missing data.
POST: Large payload handling (TC20) tests trying large pluginProperty payloads near system limits.
POST: Recovery and resilience (TC17) tests transient failures and retry behavior; integration issues (TC24) test inconsistent data handling.
POST: Edge/security scenarios (TC15 SQL injection, TC16 XSS) validate input sanitization and error handling.
POST: State variation tests (TC22, TC23) cover empty database and partially populated database scenarios.
POST: Backward compatibility (TC26) verifies missing optional fields do not break transfer.
POST: Performance scenarios (TC27–TC30) test response times, concurrency, and resource usage.
POST: Accessibility (TC31) verifies documentation and error messages are accessible.
gaps: Duplicate submission/idempotency scenarios are not covered (how to handle repeated transfer requests for the same bundle).
403 Forbidden scenarios (valid auth but insufficient permissions) are not explicitly tested.
Rate limiting / throttling scenarios are not tested.
Caching behavior and headers for POST responses (e.g., Cache-Control, ETag) are not tested.
Explicit testing for invalid data types in request body beyond the covered cases (e.g., non-string IDs, malformed pluginProperty structures) is limited.
Edge case tests around extremely large numbers of concurrent requests beyond TC29 are not covered.
recommendations: Add an idempotency/duplicate submission test to ensure repeated transfers are gracefully handled.
Add a test for 403 Forbidden when permissions are insufficient, in addition to 401 unauthorized.
Add rate limiting/throttling tests to validate SLA under bursts.
Add tests verifying caching headers or their absence for POST responses to confirm caching behavior.
Extend input validation coverage to cover additional invalid data type scenarios and malformed pluginProperty structures.
Add more robust concurrency tests beyond TC29 (e.g., race conditions with simultaneous transfers of the same bundle).
